==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tender-hearted
<hw>Ten"der-heart`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having great
sensibility; susceptible of impressions or influence; affectionate;
pitying; sensitive.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Ten"der-heart`ed*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos> -- <wf>Ten"der-heart`ed*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Rehoboam was young and <qex>tender-hearted</qex>, and could not
withstand them.</q> <rj><qau>2 Chron. xiii. 7.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Be ye kind one to another, <qex>tender-hearted</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Eph. iv. 32.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tender-hefted</ent>⟦br⟧
